1
00:00:01,589 --> 00:00:03,930
Instructor: We want to implement a repository pattern

2
00:00:03,930 --> 00:00:07,110
for data access inside our project.

3
00:00:07,110 --> 00:00:08,760
Since this is a big project,

4
00:00:08,760 --> 00:00:11,670
it is always good to have a repository pattern

5
00:00:11,670 --> 00:00:14,610
rather than accessing the database directly,

6
00:00:14,610 --> 00:00:18,333
like we are doing inside the controller right here.

7
00:00:19,260 --> 00:00:21,750
So, let me close all the tabs here,

8
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:25,410
and we will start fresh with our data access project.

9
00:00:25,410 --> 00:00:28,110
We need to create a repository.

10
00:00:28,110 --> 00:00:31,170
So, first thing first, let me create a folder here

11
00:00:31,170 --> 00:00:33,450
with the name of Repository.

12
00:00:33,450 --> 00:00:34,650
And inside there,

13
00:00:34,650 --> 00:00:38,348
we will create a folder for IRepository,

14
00:00:38,348 --> 00:00:40,260
which will hold all the interface,

15
00:00:40,260 --> 00:00:43,773
and the implementation will be inside Repository.

16
00:00:44,790 --> 00:00:49,050
So we can move our IRepository inside the Repository folder,

17
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:50,460
like that.

18
00:00:50,460 --> 00:00:52,980
So first, let me implement the interface

19
00:00:52,980 --> 00:00:55,170
inside the IRepository,

20
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:57,360
we will implement interface,

21
00:00:57,360 --> 00:01:00,150
and I will call that IRepository.

22
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:01,830
Let's add that.

23
00:01:01,830 --> 00:01:04,290
This will be a public interface,

24
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:07,350
and this interface should be generic.

25
00:01:07,350 --> 00:01:09,270
Right now, we have category,

26
00:01:09,270 --> 00:01:12,330
but as we move forward, we will have cover type,

27
00:01:12,330 --> 00:01:17,190
company, user, order header, order details, and much more.

28
00:01:17,190 --> 00:01:21,780
This repository should be able to handle all of the classes.

29
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:25,350
We can say here that this will be a generic repository

30
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:27,270
where T is a class.

31
00:01:27,270 --> 00:01:29,610
It does not matter what class it will be,

32
00:01:29,610 --> 00:01:31,770
we do not have to define that here,

33
00:01:31,770 --> 00:01:33,990
it will just be a class.

34
00:01:33,990 --> 00:01:36,750
Then it can be a category that we have right now,

35
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:39,870
or maybe order header, order details.

36
00:01:39,870 --> 00:01:41,280
We don't care about that,

37
00:01:41,280 --> 00:01:46,280
inside our repository, this will be a generic repository.

38
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:47,760
So, hypothetically,

39
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:51,273
let's assume that this T is a category for now.

40
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,340
In that case,

41
00:01:53,340 --> 00:01:57,210
what will be the common methods that we want to implement?

42
00:01:57,210 --> 00:01:58,230
To check those out,

43
00:01:58,230 --> 00:02:00,600
we can go back to our web project.

44
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:03,150
In there, we have the Controller folder.

45
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:05,190
Let me minimize that.

46
00:02:05,190 --> 00:02:07,380
And inside the controller's folder

47
00:02:07,380 --> 00:02:09,660
let's open Controller.

48
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:10,919
So you can see here,

49
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:12,690
we have an IEnumerable

50
00:02:12,690 --> 00:02:15,390
where we are getting all the categories.

51
00:02:15,390 --> 00:02:19,380
So we need to implement that here in the generic category.

52
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:23,340
Return type should be an IEnumerable of T,

53
00:02:23,340 --> 00:02:25,800
T basically can be any class,

54
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:28,560
it can be category when we are using

55
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,603
inside the category controller.

56
00:02:31,470 --> 00:02:33,870
We do not want any parameters here,

57
00:02:33,870 --> 00:02:36,540
we just want to retrieve all the categories,

58
00:02:36,540 --> 00:02:39,240
that is our first requirement.

59
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,920
Then if we scroll down,

60
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:44,280
we have a requirement to add a category.

61
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,290
So when we are adding a category,

62
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:49,350
we are passing the object that needs to be added,

63
00:02:49,350 --> 00:02:52,140
which is an object of the class.

64
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:54,780
So, let's implement that right here.

65
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:56,970
The return type will be void,

66
00:02:56,970 --> 00:02:59,040
method name, we can give it Add,

67
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,300
and in the parameter,

68
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:03,363
we will give the entity that needs to be added.

69
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:06,840
Let's go back to our controller.

70
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:09,690
Next requirement that we have is Edit,

71
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:13,443
and inside Edit, we want to find that based on the id.

72
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:17,730
Now, if you remember here, you can use directly Find,

73
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:21,630
that works if what you are finding is a primary key.

74
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,940
But if that is not a primary key,

75
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:28,113
you can use FirstOrDefault to find that based on the id.

76
00:03:29,070 --> 00:03:30,990
Of course, with FirstOrDefault,

77
00:03:30,990 --> 00:03:33,750
you need the using statement of LINQ.

78
00:03:33,750 --> 00:03:37,440
But with that, this approach will work on any column,

79
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:38,763
not just the id.

80
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:42,030
So, let's say if you want to find the category

81
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:46,530
where Name is equal to some name that you have here,

82
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:48,870
this will work with FirstOrDefault,

83
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:51,450
but it'll not work with Find.

84
00:03:51,450 --> 00:03:54,840
So rather than implementing Find in our repository,

85
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:58,443
it makes sense to implement something like FirstOrDefault.

86
00:03:59,490 --> 00:04:02,340
So we can go back to the IRepository,

87
00:04:02,340 --> 00:04:04,710
and let's implement the FirstOrDefault

88
00:04:04,710 --> 00:04:06,660
at the very beginning.

89
00:04:06,660 --> 00:04:10,080
What will be the return type of FirstOrDefault?

90
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:14,130
It'll return an object of the class that we want.

91
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:16,529
So this will be the generic class, T,

92
00:04:16,529 --> 00:04:18,899
that will be the return type.

93
00:04:18,899 --> 00:04:22,623
We can call this method as GetFirstOrDefault.

94
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:27,420
And what will be the parameter here?

95
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:30,660
The parameter that we want here is this expression,

96
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:32,610
or something similar.

97
00:04:32,610 --> 00:04:36,960
We can have this exact expression inside the parameter.

98
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:39,660
Because this is an expression inside there,

99
00:04:39,660 --> 00:04:42,990
we have a function that is handling some scenarios

100
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:45,270
and filtering data.

101
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:47,640
To implement this exact function,

102
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:50,010
if we go to our IRepository,

103
00:04:50,010 --> 00:04:52,830
we will say we want an expression here.

104
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:56,310
We'll press Control + . for LINQ.Expression,

105
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:59,040
because that is a LINQ expression.

106
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,570
Inside that expression,

107
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:03,630
we have a function where the first parameter

108
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:07,620
is the generic class, and the output will be boolean.

109
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:09,723
We will call that as filter.

110
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,930
This will be a required property

111
00:05:12,930 --> 00:05:16,290
when we are calling the GetFirstOrDefault,

112
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:19,170
because if we are recruiting only one record,

113
00:05:19,170 --> 00:05:22,410
we will always need a filter condition.

114
00:05:22,410 --> 00:05:23,243
So with that,

115
00:05:23,243 --> 00:05:27,780
we have handled this GetFirstOrDefault scenario perfectly.

116
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:29,670
We can use this if you want,

117
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:33,030
or you can un-comment the code that we had before,

118
00:05:33,030 --> 00:05:34,773
it will still work the same.

119
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,170
Next, let's scroll down.

120
00:05:37,170 --> 00:05:41,073
We have the edit post, where we are updating some record.

121
00:05:41,970 --> 00:05:43,410
Now, update is something

122
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:46,530
that will not be common for all the repository.

123
00:05:46,530 --> 00:05:48,900
Because let's say when you're updating category,

124
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,580
you have a different logic,

125
00:05:50,580 --> 00:05:52,260
when you're updating a product,

126
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:55,140
you have a different logic because you have images

127
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:57,600
that needs to be updated.

128
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,510
So update is not something that will be consistent

129
00:06:00,510 --> 00:06:03,390
across all the models that we have.

130
00:06:03,390 --> 00:06:06,690
Because of that, it makes sense not to include that

131
00:06:06,690 --> 00:06:08,853
inside the generic repository.

132
00:06:09,810 --> 00:06:13,350
So we will come back to update in the later videos.

133
00:06:13,350 --> 00:06:16,530
After that, we have Delete, in which we have Find,

134
00:06:16,530 --> 00:06:19,740
we have implemented the GetFirstOrDefault,

135
00:06:19,740 --> 00:06:22,080
and we have the POST action method

136
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:24,510
where we are removing something.

137
00:06:24,510 --> 00:06:28,050
Inside Remove here, we just want to remove an entity,

138
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:32,490
so we have to pass that, and the return type will be void.

139
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:34,800
So we can copy the Add here,

140
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,543
paste it again for Remove.

141
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:41,190
Lastly, it is possible you want to remove

142
00:06:41,190 --> 00:06:42,870
more than one entity,

143
00:06:42,870 --> 00:06:46,233
so for that, we have something called as RemoveRange.

144
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:48,930
When we want to RemoveRange,

145
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:51,630
we will receive more than one entity here,

146
00:06:51,630 --> 00:06:53,400
so rather than T here,

147
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:56,430
we will receive an IEnumerable of T,

148
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:58,863
which is a collection of entities.

149
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:03,540
So with that, our generic repository looks good.

150
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:05,340
As we proceed with the course,

151
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:07,620
we will face some complex scenarios,

152
00:07:07,620 --> 00:07:11,043
and we will come back here to modify our repository.

153
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:15,183
So with that, let's continue from the next video.

